	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I didn't know anyone programmed it 2 different algorithms for the same type of collision.</div><br />It's obviously not mandatory, but when you have limited processing power, it might be interesting to write more specialized functions for the simpler cases, instead of using the more complex routine for everything. This is true for everything, not only collision detection. Physics, for example, is usually more complex for the main character, while other objects use simpler logic.

		

